H0.text: The menstrual cycle occurs in women of reproductive age as long as a sperm does not enter an egg.

H1.text: The extraction cycle occurs in women of reproductive age as long as a sperm does not enter an egg.

H2.text: The tissue cycle occurs in women of reproductive age as long as a sperm does not enter an egg.

H3.text: Menopausal cycle is the cycle that occurs in women of reproductive age as long as a sperm does not enter an egg.

A4.text: If implantation does not occur, the lining breaks down and blood is released.

A5.text: The menstrual cycle is a series of natural changes that make pregnancy possible.
